
[1]encouragement

   ENCOUR'AGEMENT, n. The act of giving courage, or confidence of success;
   incitement to action or to practice; incentive. We ought never to
   neglect the encouragement of youth in generous deeds. The praise of
   good men serves as an encouragement of virtue and heroism.

   1. That which serves to incite, support, promote or advance, as favor,
   countenance, rewards, profit. A young man attempted the practice of
   law, but found little encouragement. The fine arts find little
   encouragement among a rude people.
